From 8e67717e1f16b3a90c6db3f6a0e3e9f364e1971c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tal Regev <tal.regev@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 21:24:14 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] gegl, libs, tools: use def files for all Windows builds

Use the existing Windows .def files for MinGW/MSYS2 as well as MSVC,
and mark exported data symbols with DATA so Windows linkers handle them
correctly.

Add GEGL_VAR for exported data declarations, so MSVC consumers import
those symbols through the generated import library while GEGL_COMPILATION
avoids importing symbols from the library itself.

Drop private underscore-prefixed helper symbols from the public .def file.
Keep the OpenCL acceleration state private behind gegl_cl_is_accelerated(),
and make the float epsilon helpers inline so consumers no longer need
private exported symbols.

Update defcheck.py to parse .def files explicitly, ignore DATA attributes,
and validate MinGW cross-build DLL exports.
